INSERT INTO `risk_exception_tbl` VALUES (8,'Single Sign One','Globant makes use of a single authorative directory for all authentication (and most of authorization) purposes in order to simply and stronger the management of user directories. Its understood that the disadvantages of this approach is that obtaining a single credential might give to the user more access. As long as the systems which make use of the centralized directory enforce good security practices and ideally authorization of its own we are fine with approving this exception.','GIST','2013-04-18',0),(9,'Mobile Encryption at Rest','Due to performance issues encryption of mobile devices at rest resulted not possible. In order to compensate this vulnerability we have ensured that strong passwords have been enforced on all mobile systems.','GIST','2013-04-03',0),(10,'Full CCTV Coverage','There has been a need of limiting vandalism and theft across Globant sites by covering %100 of the space with CCTV systems. Due cost limitations these option has not been viable to implement. The loss of assets amounts still to relative low numbers (50k / year).','GIST','2013-12-18',0),(11,'PBX User Management','Users on the PBX are not centralized managed so theres limited capabilities in terms of changing passwords (password strength is good tough). This could lead to brute force attacks DOS and potentially breach of an extension and make use of that extension for unlimited calls. The implementation of a central directory is in planned and until is not working well review logs on daily bases.','GIST','2013-04-10',0),(12,'Digital Certificates','The implementation of Digital Certificates and Signatures at Globant is a solution still not implemented and thereby the implementation of such technology on e-mails vpn connections etc is not possible.','GIST','2013-04-24',0),(13,'Tape Custodians - Third Party','Backup Tapes custodians is a third party for which we have assessed risks (#3 from the Third Party Risk Assesment) and for which the company has accepted that in case of destruction theft or loss of the tapes by the third party the contractual agreements which include penalties will suffice. This has been considered on this way since Globant has no better ways to protect those tapes.','GIST','2013-07-18',0),(14,'Datacenter - Third Party','Our datacenters are managed by third parties given the complexity that such infrastructure requires. Globant has contracts with them and their SLAs assure that their physical controls (dealing energy enviromental temperature cctv access to our systems etc) are in place and functional. Tests of such controls is not possible (we reviewed this with them) given the contracts we have in place so we have to conform ourselves with the SLAs they provide. This is documented on the third party risk analysis on #1 #2','GIST','2013-07-13',0),(15,'Laminar Entry Log Book','We do not manage the security of Laminar premises at the entrance of the building since its part of the leasing agreement. Control of the people who has access to the building is on their hands. We accept this risk since anyway even when people could access our floors they would have the need for a valid proximity card. The third party risk assessment that relates to this risk exception is #10.','GIST','2013-07-15',0),(16,'Linux/Apple systems USB block','90% of our devices used to be Microsoft orientated but since Globant recently acquired other companies that used Apple devices we must develop a policy in order to control de use of USB mass storage devices. This is an improvement that is already planned and will be completed by Q3 2013.','GIST','2013-07-18',0),(17,'Customer End-Point Security Policies','Some of Globant customers provide security policies for the systems which interact with their software servers mobile applications etc. This means that Globant is not allowed to modify the configuration of this assets even if their settings are not aligned with Globant security policies.','GIST','2013-08-18',0),(18,'Google Services','Google has been the official provider of cloud services for Globant in all related matters around email and file storage. Their cost  benefit ratio is way beyond the reach of Globant IT teams.','esteban.ribicic','2013-12-18',0);
